			    STPJS 314</div>
  <p class="cont">the Gospel of salvation<span class="footRef">1</span> which he revealed? So do I. Christians should cease wrangling and
  contending<span class="footRef">2</span> with each other, and cultivate the principles of union and friendship in their midst;
  and they will do it before the millennium can be ushered in and Christ takes possession of His
  kingdom.<span class="footRef">3</span></p>
  <p class="std">&ldquo;Do you believe in the baptism of infants?&rdquo;<span class="footRef">4</span> asks the Presbyterian. No. &ldquo;Why?&rdquo; Because it
  is nowhere written in the Bible. Circumcision is not baptism,<span class="footRef">5</span> neither was baptism instituted in
  the place of circumcision. Baptism is for remission of sins.<span class="footRef">6</span> Children have no sins.<span class="footRef">7</span> Jesus blessed
  them<span class="footRef">8</span> and said, &ldquo;Do what you have seen me do.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">9</span> Children are all made alive in Christ,<span class="footRef">10</span> and
  those of riper years through faith and repentance.<span class="footRef">11</span></p>
  <p class="std">So far we are agreed with other Christian denominations. They all preach faith and
  repentance.<span class="footRef">12</span> The gospel<span class="footRef">13</span> requires baptism by immersion for the remission of sins,<span class="footRef">14</span> which is the
  meaning of the word in the original language&mdash;namely, to bury or immerse.<span class="footRef">15</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Necessity of Ordinances</div>
  <p class="std">We ask the sects, Do you believe this? They answer, No. I believe in being converted. I believe
  in this tenaciously. So did the Apostle Peter and the disciples of Jesus.<span class="footRef">16</span> But I further believe in the
  gift of the Holy Ghost by the laying on of hands.<span class="footRef">17</span> Evidence by Peter&rsquo;s preaching on the day of
  Pentecost, Acts 2:38.<span class="footRef">18</span> You might as well baptize a bag of sand as a man,<span class="footRef">19</span> if not done in view of
  the remission of sins and getting of the Holy Ghost.<span class="footRef">20</span> Baptism by water is but half a baptism, and
  is good for nothing without the other half&mdash;that is, the baptism of the Holy Ghost.<span class="footRef">21</span></p>
  <p class="std">The Savior says, &ldquo;Except a man be born of water and of the Spirit, he cannot enter into the
  kingdom of God.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">22</span> &ldquo;Though we or an angel from heaven, preach any other gospel unto you than
  that which we have preached unto you, let him be accursed,&rdquo; according to Galatians 1:8.<span class="footRef">23</span> (July 9,
  1843.) DHC 5:498–500.</p>
  <div class="topic">Discourse&mdash;Burden of the Prophet&rsquo;s Ministry&mdash;Friendship</div>
  <p class="std">I commence my remarks by reading this text&mdash;Luke 16:16: &ldquo;The law and the prophets were
  until John: since that time the kingdom of God is preached, and every man presseth into it.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">24</span></p>
  <p class="std">I do not know that I shall be able to preach much; but,</p>
